description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join a new team of staff who will focus their time on delivering a COVID swabbing service. This service operates as a drive-through service where staff members or patients attending for surgery or treatment will be swabbed for COVID 48-72 hours prior to their treatment date. There are two drive-through centres, one in Grimsby and one in Scunthorpe, you will be flexible and able to work across both sites. Both sites operate Monday to Sunday 0830-1630hrs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full training will be provided including training for the appropriate use of PPE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This contract is offered on a fixed term basis for up to 3 months depending upon start date and the contract will end on March 2021, with regular reviews being conducted regarding continuing the service for a longer period if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that the job description added is generic and includes the general tasks related to a band 2 post rather than a specific job description relating to the swabbing service. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maria Briggs, Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: maria.briggs3@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07710075161&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jackie Fenwick, Team Leader, Unplanned Services&lt;/p&gt;
